}} 'Quadratics' is a six-part Canadian instructional television series produced
by TVOntario in 1993. The miniseries is part of the Concepts in Mathematics
series. The program uses computer animation to demonstrate quadratic equations
and their corresponding functions in the Cartesian coordinate system.<ref></ref>
